        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 5:11PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rockingham, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dobbins Heights, Pinehurst, Hoffman, Aberdeen, Pinebluff, Sandhills
Game Land, Camp Mackall, Ellerbe, East Rockingham, and Rockingham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
